Superior parietal sulcus.SuperCategory: Superficial feature part of parietal cortex
Superior parietal sulcus.Definition: The term superior parietal sulcus (H) refers to a superficial feature of the parietal lobe that extends from the dorsal surface of the superior parietal lobule across the margin of the parietal lobe into the precuneus (Ono-90). (NN)
